name: SUNY Oneonta Campus
directions:
There are several gender neutral bathrooms on the SUNY Oneonta campus. If you are visiting the campus, you'll likely be using one of these two:
-In the Fine Arts building (which is where you will be if you are attending a show at the Goodrich or Hamblin theaters), there are a set of gendered bathrooms in the east hallway; follow the hallway south through a set of double doors (don't be shy if they are closed), and there will be a gender neutral bathroom on your right, near the water fountain. 
-In Hunt Union, which is the most public of the buildings on campus, there is one on the ground floor. It's hard to find, it is down a hallway to the right of the Waterfront room.
comment: http://www.oneonta.edu/development/gsrc/bathrooms.asp

name: Park Region
directions: Must have fob access to the Park Region dorms. Bathrooms are on the 2nd and basement floors.
comment:
There are two gender neutral bathrooms in this dorm. The older one is in the basement and can be accessed by stairs or elevator. It only holds a toilet and a sink but can be nice for use if you are studying or visiting here.
The newer one was installed in 2014 and is on the 2nd floor (ground level) of the dorm. It has a toilet, a sink, and a shower. All of them are nicely separated. It also has a very nice lock. My favorite bathroom on the whole campus. Demand can get a little higher since it also contains a shower and is meant for singe occupancy.

name: Detroit Zoo
directions:
There are two restrooms at the zoo I would recommend-
1. The Ford Education Center, which is the big building next to Rackham Fountain towards the center of the zoo
2. The restrooms attached to Sweet Treats, and ice cream place between the Arctic Ring of Life and the giraffes. (Across from the bears).
comment:
1. FEC restrooms are gendered, but the restrooms on the second floor (which are also open to the public) are usually deserted. Lights are motion activated so if the lights are off when you walk in, you know no ones been in there for at least 10 minutes or something.
2. Sweet Treats restrooms are gender inclusive family restrooms, with stalls but the actual door to the whole restroom locks as well. There may be a line though.
